The paper discusses the learning dynamics of neural nets, which is a core topic in machine learning. The focus is on linear and multi-layer neural nets, which are commonly used in various applications such as computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also touches on the non-linear dynamics of ReLU neural nets, which is relevant to the field of cs.SI (Systems and Control). Finally, the application of the theory to computer vision suggests a possible connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
